I was introduced by my WWIi vet grandpa that passed away at 98 years old this past January. I frequented this restaurant wkly , 2014-27....grandpa requested oxtails for lunch every Saturday and was generally disappointed when the restaurant closed Veterans Day 2017. In memory of my gpa I purchased oxtails last night 12/16.... I opened my meal tonight and was disappointed to find the majority of the oxtails were burnt. I ate the 4 that were not burnt but,  the flavor was as amazing as ever. For $15 in the hood the server should have been aware of the burnt meat and not sold it to me.
